# Components

## Server vs Client

Default to Server Components. Add `'use client'` only when the component needs:

- Event handlers (`onClick`, `onChange`)
- React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`)
- Browser APIs (`window`, `localStorage`)

Push the client boundary as far down the tree as possible.

```tsx
// âœ… GOOD â€” small client island inside server page
export default async function EventPage({ params }: Props) {
  const event = await getEvent(params.id)
  return (
    <div>
      <EventHeader event={event} />
      <JoinFightButton eventId={event.id} />
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Forms

- Prefer `<form action={serverAction}>` over manual fetch calls
- Use `useActionState` for action feedback (pending, errors, success)
- Use `useFormStatus` in a child submit button for loading state
- For instant feedback on high-confidence mutations (join, toggle), see `optimistic-ui.mdc`

## Composition

- Keep components under ~150 lines; extract subcomponents when growing
- Colocate feature-specific components in `features/{module}/components/`
- Shared UI primitives live in `components/ui/` (shadcn)

## Styling

- Tailwind utility classes; use `cn()` from `lib/utils` for conditional classes
- Do not use inline styles except for dynamic values